.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.CONCEALMENTEVENTS" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.concealmentEvents \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
concealmentEvents property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]concealmentEvents\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the total
number of concealment events for the received audio track over the
lifetime of this stats object.
.PP
A concealed sample is a sample that was lost or arrived too late to be
played out, and therefore had to be replaced with a locally generated
synthesized sample.
Any number of consecutive concealed samples following a non\-concealed
sample comprise a single concealment event.
The value in this property will therefore be less than or equal to
\f[CR]concealedSamples\f[R], which counts every sample.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The value is undefined for video streams.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A positive integer.
.SH SEE ALSO
